World Health Organization’s Director-General, Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus is briefing the media. This follows his visit to a WHO-backed mRNA tech transfer hub in South Africa. During the visit, Tedros was joined by Belgium’s Minister of Development Cooperation Meryame Kitir and hosted by South Africa’s Health Minister Joe Phaahla and Deputy Science and Innovation Minister Buti Manamela. LIVE: WHO’s Dr Tedros Ghebreyesus briefs media following visit to SA’s vaccination sites  